instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "Digital Twin development follows a Model‑Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) lifecycle organized into four abstraction layers: requirements specification, functional architecture, logical architecture, and product/technical layer. At each level SysML-based models (e.g., component‑connector diagrams, state machines) capture the system’s structure and behavior. Transition between phases is governed by MBSE artefacts: a SysML IBD (integrated block diagram) at the functional level is mapped to a logical model defined in an architecture description language such as AADL or MontiArc, and further mapped to a product/technical model implemented in Simulink or generated C++/Java code. Lifecycle governance is facilitated by maintaining synchronized MBSE artefacts across levels and by adopting process frameworks such as RFLP or SMArDT."
]

